Modern advertising only arrived here in 1989, so already in the era you speak of. Right from the start there was very little originality - the ads were full of fakely smiling families, bad music and bad sslogans. Exceptions were few and far between, and generally involved references to Polish culture and clever use of our language rather than simply copying American tropes.

